title: Riley’s 32 anchors EU win over Sierra
text:
Home › SPORTS › High School Sports › Riley’s 32 anchors EU win over Sierra Riley’s 32 anchors EU win over Sierra Tweet 
Brooke Riley was two strokes shy of tying her own record at the Manteca Park Golf Course front nine in a Valley Oak League dual match with Sierra.East Union’s standout missed birdie putts on the seventh and eighth holes, settling for a still-impressive five-under 32 while leading the Lancers’ 229-252 win.She’ll now set out to win the individual title for a third time in today’s Sierra Invitational held at Manteca Park Golf course. The Lancers have claimed the last seven team championships.Sierra’s McKenna Doyle finished 5-over for the second lowest score Tuesday. Backing up Riley’s 32 for East Union, which improved to 11-0 in the VOL, were Allie Tajii (46), Rebeca Leonard (49), Brittany Conjin (50), Chloe Cardenas (52) and Natalie Cardenas (52).Sierra (8-5) got contributions from Legacy Barnes (49), Arlena Gavino (51), Kayla Wilson (55) and Bryanna Gavino (55). CollegeBig 8 ConferenceNAPA — Sierra graduate Lexus Barnes shot a 21-over 94 to help Delta Junior college place fourth with a 375 in a Big 8 Conference tournament. Sierra (348), Modesto (363) and Butte (374) were the top three teams. Manteca alumna Katie Hankins also plays for Delta.
